metadata.name: The Swindler
metadata.description:
1/1 tied to PHYSICAL PAINTING 

The Swindler
oil and acrylic on canvas
48" x 60" (4' x 5')

The genius stared 
With soft tender eyes.
All his characters merged,
What a pleasant disguise.
Behind his many faces
Lay a sweet gentle soul,
Who only wanted to be seen
Beyond his lead role.
The artist within
Knew not of his fame,
He only wanted to escape 
This life we call a game. 
There is no great genius 
Without a touch of madness
The key to all his greatness 
is hidden in his sadness.
 
email studio@zoeschwartz.com after purchasing, to arrange for shipping. ships as a rolled canvas.
